-- Chinese Police Detain 3 at Cantonese Rally in Guangzhou, Xinhua Reports
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-02T23:50:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/chinese-police-detain-3-at-cantonese-rally-in-guangzhou-xinhua-reports.html

          
          
             Chinese police detained three people
at a rally in the southern city of Guangzhou on Aug. 1 that was
held to call on the government to preserve the local Cantonese
dialect, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.  
 The two men and one woman were detained for disrupting
public order, Xinhua reported late yesterday, citing local
police.  
          
          


  


        